rules:
{"pattern": "chest pain.*(shortness|breathing|dizzy|dizziness)", "response": "URGENT: Chest pain accompanied by breathing difficulty or dizziness could indicate a heart issue. Please seek emergency care immediately. Do not wait for an appointment.", "priority": 100}
{"pattern": "chest pain|chest hurts|chest tight", "response": "Chest pain can have various causes from muscle strain to heart issues. Given you are experiencing this after exertion, I recommend you see a doctor today. Have you had any other symptoms like shortness of breath, dizziness, or nausea?", "priority": 80}
{"pattern": "dizzy|dizziness|lightheaded", "response": "Dizziness combined with chest pain is a concerning combination. It could suggest your heart is not pumping effectively. Please mention this to a healthcare provider as soon as possible.", "priority": 70}
{"pattern": "(breathing|breathless|short.*breath|catch.*breath)", "response": "Shortness of breath with chest pain needs immediate evaluation. Is this getting worse when you walk or talk? If so, please go to the ER.", "priority": 75}
{"pattern": "(fever|temperature|chills|sweating)", "response": "A fever alongside chest pain could indicate an infection or inflammation like pericarditis. Have you checked your temperature? Let your doctor know.", "priority": 60}
{"pattern": "what should|should I|what do|recommend|advise", "response": "Based on what you described -- intermittent chest pain with shortness of breath and dizziness -- you should be evaluated today. Visit an urgent care center or call your primary care provider. If symptoms worsen, call 911.", "priority": 90}

{"pattern": "(don'?t|didn'?t|never|not).*(recognize|authorize|approve|make|know)", "response": "I understand this charge does not look familiar. Let me look it up. Your account shows a Basic plan at $19.99/mo. The $49.99 Premium Plan Upgrade charge is unusual. I will flag this to our billing team for investigation. Would you like to also dispute this charge?", "priority": 100}
{"pattern": "(Premium|Upgrade|$49|49.99|49\\.99)", "response": "I can see the $49.99 Premium Plan Upgrade charge on May 15th. This does not match your current Basic plan. I will escalate this as an unauthorized change to your account.", "priority": 80}
{"pattern": "refund|remove|cancel.*charge|reverse", "response": "I can request a refund for this charge. Since it was unauthorized and from May 15th (within 30 days), it should qualify. I will initiate the refund process. You should see the credit within 5-7 business days.", "priority": 70}
{"pattern": "(fraud|stolen|identity|unauthorized|not.*mine)", "response": "I will treat this as a potentially unauthorized transaction. Let me document the charge and escalate to our fraud team. In the meantime, monitor your account for other suspicious activity and change your account password.", "priority": 90}
{"pattern": "(Basic|basic|$19|19\\.99|my plan|current plan)", "response": "You are correct. Your account is on the Basic tier at $19.99/mo. The $49.99 Premium Plan Upgrade was applied on May 15th without a plan change request. This appears to be an error on our end.", "priority": 70}
{"pattern": "(contact|speak|talk|human|person|agent|manager)", "response": "I understand you may want to speak with someone directly. I have noted your request and escalated this to our billing department. A specialist will reach out within 24 hours. Your case reference is BILL-2026-0515.", "priority": 50}
{"pattern": "(thank|thanks|appreciate|helpful)", "response": "You are welcome. I have initiated the refund for the unauthorized $49.99 Premium Plan Upgrade charge. You will receive a confirmation email shortly. Is there anything else I can help with?", "priority": 30}
